reviewText:
We actually own all of the Paw Patrol dvd's, they are always excellent, and this one doesn't disappoint. My son and daughter both adore this show!! This is one of the few shows that they will actually watch all the way through without walking away to go play. These dvd's are always worth the money!!!!

Episodes:
1. Pups Pit Crew
2. Pups Fight Fire
3. Pups Save A Hoedown
4. Pups Save Alex
5. Pups Save A Monkey
6. Pups Save A Hoot
7. Pups And The Lighthouse Boogie
8. Pups Save Ryder

Bonus: Pup, Pup, and Away! - Video Storybook

Side note: DVD is playable in English, Spanish or French

My girls love Paw Patrol. This DVD contains eight half-length episodes from the Nickelodeon cartoon. Amazon doesn't always do a good job on their DVD episode listings so here are the episodes that are included on this DVD:

1. Pups Pit Crew - Pups must save Alex after he goes too fast on his Super-trike.
2. Pups Fight Fire - Marshall has problems when he tries to break the record for the world's fastest fire-pup.
3. Pups Save a Hoedown -  Farmer Al's cows escape and must be stopped before they stampede over the hoedown.
4. Pups Save Alex - The Paw Patrol must rescue a cat stuck on top of a silo.
5. Pups Save a Monkey - The team must catch an escaped monkey.
6. Pups Save a Hoot - The team must save an owl from a falling tree.
7. Pups and the Lighthouse Boogie - A storm sets boats adrift and the Paw Patrol must save them.
8. Pups Save Ryder - Ryder needs help after a rescue gone wrong.

Bonus Features
1. Video Storybook - Pup, Pup, and Away!

My three-year-old twins love Paw Patrol and they received this DVD for Christmas. We have all of the other Paw Patrol DVDs that are currently available and they repeatedly ask to watch them, so much so that I think to myself "Really??? Again?!?!?!" They never get tired of watching the same episodes over again so it is nice to have another DVD to add to our collection! I have watched this show with them a number of times and I think it's great for children of all ages. I also think this show is perfect for both boys and girls and it keeps my kids from fighting over what they want to watch! It's about a group of puppies and their ten-year-old fearless leader, Ryder, who help the citizens of Adventure Bay and keep the community safe.

This particular DVD contains 92 minutes worth of eight episodes, each approximately 11 minutes long. The description doesn't list the episode names so I will list them here:

Pups Pit Crew
Pups Fight Fire
Pups Save a Hoedown
Pups Save Alex
Pups Save a Monkey
Pups Save a Hoot
Pups and the Lighthouse Boogie
Pups Save Ryder

I love that each of the four DVDs currently available don't overlap any episodes so you don't have to worry about repeats. Please note that this DVD doesn't contain any episodes with Everest, the newest pup, so if your children like her, you will want to be sure to purchase the DVD entitled Meet Everest! This DVD contains an additional feature of the Pup, Pup, and Away! video storybook and this DVD can be watched in English, Spanish, and French.

I think this DVD is a great addition to our Paw Patrol collection and my kids love this show! It keeps their attention, it's very safe for them to watch (I'm very cautious about what they watch), and even I enjoy watching the puppies and their adventures. I highly recommend this DVD and the Paw Patrol show for anyone who has young children!
